Dow drops 186 points on losses for Coca-Cola, United Technologies stocks


Dragged down by declines for shares of Coca-Cola and United Technologies, the Dow Jones Industrial Average is declining Thursday morning. Shares of Coca-Cola KO, +0.12% and United Technologies UTX are contributing to the index's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 186 points (0.9%) lower. Coca-Cola's shares are off $2.69 (6.0%) while those of United Technologies have dropped $3.92 (5.0%), combining for a roughly 45-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include Johnson & Johnson JNJ, -0.84%, Procter & Gamble PG, -0.06%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.48%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the benchmark equates to a 6.78-point swing.

